        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 4:19PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 5 miles west of Willard to near Fort
Morgan, or extending from 21 miles west of Sterling to near Fort
Morgan, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Log Lane Village, Hillrose, Snyder, Midway,
Gary, Antelope Springs, Adena School, Prewitt Reservoir, Union,
Messex and Fort Morgan Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
